The United States congratulates the United Arab Emirates (UAE) for being selected as the host of the 2020 World Expo, marking the first time it will be held in the Middle East. The UAE's selection highlights its role as a business hub and global crossroads for Africa and Asia, showcasing its leadership in innovation and entrepreneurship. The UAE is an important trade and investment partner for the United States, and recent agreements between UAE airlines and Boeing will create jobs and further strengthen the commercial relationship between the two countries.